### PHP Form URL Validation

URL validation ensures user-provided URLs are properly formatted.

### Using filter_var

```php
<?php
$url = "https://example.com";
if (filter_var($url, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL)) {
    echo "$url is a valid URL";
} else {
    echo "$url is not a valid URL";
}
?>
```

### Complete URL Validation

```php
<?php
$website = $websiteErr = "";

if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    if (empty($_POST["website"])) {
        $websiteErr = "Website is required";
    } else {
        $website = trim($_POST["website"]);
        if (!preg_match("/^https?:\/\//", $website)) {
            $website = "https://" . $website; // Add default scheme
        }
        if (!filter_var($website, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL)) {
            $websiteErr = "Invalid URL format";
        }
    }
}
?>
```

### URL Validation Options

| Filter/Option | Description |
|---------------|-------------|
| `FILTER_VALIDATE_URL` | Validates URL format |
| `FILTER_FLAG_PATH_REQUIRED` | URL must have a path |
| `FILTER_FLAG_QUERY_REQUIRED` | URL must have a query string |

```php
<?php
$url = "https://example.com/page?q=test";

// URL with path required
if (filter_var($url, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL, FILTER_FLAG_PATH_REQUIRED)) {
    echo "URL with path is valid";
}

// URL with query required
if (filter_var($url, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL, FILTER_FLAG_QUERY_REQUIRED)) {
    echo "URL with query is valid";
}
?>
```

### Sanitize URL

```php
<?php
$url = "javascript:alert('xss')";
$clean = filter_var($url, FILTER_SANITIZE_URL);
// Removes invalid URL characters
echo $clean;
?>
```

> **Key Point:** `FILTER_VALIDATE_URL` checks format only, not whether the URL actually exists. Use `get_headers()` to check if a URL is reachable.
